.SH SECURITY CONSIDERATIONS
The \-\-fix option makes system changes. Always:
.IP 1 4
Review changes before applying
.IP 2 4
Have a backup or snapshot available
.IP 3 4
Test SSH access in a new session before closing current session
.IP 4 4
Verify node functionality after applying fixes
.PP
The security command cannot protect against all threats. Follow the complete
XDC security guide at:
https://github.com/AnilChinchawale/xdc-node-setup/blob/main/SECURITY.md
